<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by DevilsPuppet:
[I]I just picked this game up yesterday and it is the best RPG I have played since Wizardry 8. I'm glad there are still companies willing to make good old fashioned RPG's. I am even happier that there are enough folks out there that still like to play them. I thought I was just getting old, hehe.

Anyway, I have a few questions I couldn't really figure out about the game. Any help would be greatly appreciated.

1. Can you store items in containers? For example is it safe to fill up the chests in the room you begin the game in, or will the items dissapear?

2. If you steal stuff from an NPC's house and he is out or not watching, does he ever find out, or will it affect reputation in anyway later?

3. Are quest items ever unidentified? And will shop keepers give you more money for items that you identify and repair before selling (Like Diablo 2)?

4. Does being nice to the orcs in the begining dungeon effect your reputation negativly?

Any help would be appreciated, thanks in advance  :)
[/I][/QUOTE]

