 be visible on screen.<P>3, I think all the quest items are identified already...again my poor memory is hazy on this point!! You'll get more money after identifying if it's good. Usually yes but very rarely I got less after ID'ing the item.<P>4, Don't be nice to the orcs...grrrr.....I didn't give them the axe and went back when I was powerful enough and kicked their butts!!!  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Hope that's not completely unhelpful!!  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">mslynx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have a whole room full of chests and vases that I keep weapons etc. in. I love home decorating. The items stay right where you put them.<BR>As far as stealing...What they don't know won't hurt you.<BR>I really haven't noticed if the price for items is better after you repair them...I would imagine so.(that is something I will check out,thanx) <A HREF="http://mywebpage.netscape.com/mslynx03/index.html" TARGET=_blank>http://mywebpage.netscape.com/mslynx03/index.html</A> <P>------------------<BR>Step away from your senses.Your senses blind you.<BR>[This message has been edited by mslynx (edited 29-10-2002).]<p>[This message has been edited by mslynx (edited 29-10-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DevilsPuppet</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cool, thanks for the replies  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"> I was just getting tired of trying to pawn off my garbage to the shop keeper with limited income, hehe<BR><P>------------------<BR>DevilsPuppet</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jim Overflowed</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">1. Yes it's save<BR>2. If they don't see it you can steal what you want.<BR>3. Some quest items can be unidentified, but generally you'll know what quest items are and what not.<BR>4. Identifying items before selling is almost always worth it (since it costs only 150 if you don't have the skills yourself). Repairing is not.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">cosmo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I know not al quest items are identified . Slasher wasn't identified .</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Plowking</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I actually never found Slasher...I went back to the orcs when I was level 30 with a cheap axe I bought off a merchant and gave that to the orcs so they'd attack me!! I kicked their ugly green hides all over the place!!<P>Whoo-hoo..... <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/biggrin.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Founding member of the Rivellon Against Frogs Society (RAFS)...join me, together we can wipe out this menace!!</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">the bean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by mslynx:<BR>I really haven't noticed if the price for items is better after you repair them...I would imagine so.(that is something I will check out,thanx) <BR>[/I]<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>i checkes it out some few days ago..<BR>i was thinking is it worth repairing those weapons??<P>example: i have a claymore sword durability 5/15<BR>kost of this sword damaged 500<BR>when i reaired it kost me 1100 golds.. now the price is 1500 golds for the repaired sword...<P>you would think, hé i give 1100 gols and get 1000 back??? soo you loose 100 gold coins...<P>only if the reputation is 100 of the npc, it will repair the item so you wouldn't spend anny gold to it..(so you pay 1000 golds, but get 1000gold more worthit on the item)<P>tip, always use otto the dwarf from the first village, his status quickely goes to 100 if you repair some weapons from him.....<P>i did this test with a level 3 barther skill, but i think it hasnt anny to do with it...</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">E-Hyvel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Jim Overflowed:<BR>[I](since it costs only 150 if you don't have the skills yourself). I]<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Nitpicking: If the npc likes you, it can be cheaper as well...but I think 100 is the minimum.<P>------------------<BR>Being paranoid doesn't mean you're not being followed.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">WindForce</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">e,i think it's about ALL quest item is unidentified...just like the sword of the stone,the most powerful sword,i'd get one with 5lv stun,5lv poison,5lv frost,5lv spirit and 4lv life drain....to quick save/load,then you get it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">mslynx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">mmm...Don't know about the sword in the stone thing,but thanks for the heads up on the repair weapons befor selling...Never know when the extra cash might come in handy !  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Step away from your senses.Your senses blind you.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DE</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When you get an unidentified item, it will tell you the level. The higher the level, the more valuable. You won't get a tiny fraction of the value if you don't identify, so with rare exeception you will alway come out way ahead when you identify anything that is level 2 or greater. For instance an unidentifed level two ring, might be worth 30 gold, but when you identify it, it a dimound ring, with 2 charm and some status boast and now it is worth 2500 gold. Plus you won't be able to wear an item until it is identified, so you aren't going to have powerful equipment without identifing it.<P>Sometimes you come out ahead when you pay to repair things, but most of the time you come out a little behind. Of course the best thing is to have some skill points in repair, in which case you always make money. A nice item in close to perfect condition is worth many, many times more then one in poor condition. For instance a 1/25 level 3 sword might be worth 175 gold, the same sword at 11/25 1700, and the same sword 25/25 8700. I'm making these number up just to give you a rough idea of much of a difference the condition makes in price. The higher potential condition, the more the condition matters.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</IFRAME>
